                "notes": "Verify the application is working by running these commands:\n  kubectl --namespace aarnn port-forward service/aarnn-net-loki 3100\n  curl http://127.0.0.1:3100/api/prom/label\n\nThe Loki stack has been deployed to your cluster. Loki can now be added as a datasource in Grafana.\n\nSee http://docs.grafana.org/features/datasources/loki/ for more detail.\n\n***********************************************************************\n Welcome to Grafana Promtail\n Chart version: 6.15.5\n Promtail version: 2.9.3\n***********************************************************************\n\nVerify the application is working by running these commands:\n* kubectl --namespace aarnn port-forward daemonset/aarnn-net-loki-promtail 3101\n* curl http://127.0.0.1:3101/metrics\n",
                "revision": 1,
                "values": "{\"grafana\":{\"enabled\":false},\"loki\":{\"isDefault\":true,\"service\":{\"type\":\"ClusterIP\"}},\"promtail\":{\"enabled\":true,\"service\":{\"type\":\"ClusterIP\"}}}",
